    {
      "id": "3899f000c38f841b49c1324b7f08a2f405bb8c9d",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2013-07-11 05:40:19.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nhow is this better than http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/5471/ ?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "03df09877bc8a65c8bc7a5578d5d89be313e1784",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 229,
        "name": "Bruno Faccini",
        "email": "bfaccini@nvidia.com",
        "username": "bfaccini"
      },
      "date": "2013-07-11 08:30:57.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nBecause as I already commented negatively for Prakash's change #6790 for this same LU-3504, doing FLock related hashing stuff allocation in ldlm_init_export() will cause it to be allocated for all types of exports when it is only required for MDTs and then not for all clients/exports. It is why I decided to do it during 1st FLock on export.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "eb414326e4e7e3973262dc3c3679192c8b688d08",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 229,
        "name": "Bruno Faccini",
        "email": "bfaccini@nvidia.com",
        "username": "bfaccini"
      },
      "date": "2013-07-11 08:32:15.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nIf you agree on this, may be I/you should also comment on this in Change #5471 ??",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "83ce8ed5dfb17f3d1116597f94beb0f06a07c360",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 124,
        "name": "Prakash Surya",
        "email": "lists@prakashsurya.com",
        "username": "prakash"
      },
      "date": "2013-07-15 15:01:58.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nBruno, if you look at #5471, they add some logic to restrict the allocation to MDTs only:\n\n\n    if( strcmp(exp->exp_obd->obd_type->typ_name, LUSTRE_MDT_NAME) != 0)\t850\n        RETURN(0);\n\nI think that addresses your concerns, although I'm not convinced it's any cleaner than this solution. Since that patch was introduced to fix a race, I'm curious if this patch suffers from the same race as the original code?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "751253dc70591172ee6d4be6a34a69048dc6f7c7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 229,
        "name": "Bruno Faccini",
        "email": "bfaccini@nvidia.com",
        "username": "bfaccini"
      },
      "date": "2013-07-15 15:27:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nSure, and I better detailed on this already in my last comment in LU-3504. Only difference, I think, is unconditional allocation for all MDT-exports vs upon 1st need. Each having respectively a memory and a cpu/test cost.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "86fb369fe75c6479e679f1dc9785a18eb2db5f25",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 229,
        "name": "Bruno Faccini",
        "email": "bfaccini@nvidia.com",
        "username": "bfaccini"
      },
      "date": "2013-07-31 07:32:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Abandoned\n\nPatch abandonned in benefit of change http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/5471/ from LU-2835, as per reviewers/gatekeeper decision.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    }
  ],
